<hl>
<seg id=1> Chinese enterprises become the biggest foreign investors in Macao. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Macao, April 3rd, by Zhiken Wang and Yumin Che -The Macao Chinese Enterprises Association President Yimin Zhang said that, currently there are more than 200 Chinese Enterprises in Macao.  The total amount of invested capital has exceeded 90 billion Yuan in Macao currency. </seg>
<seg id=3> Chinese enterprises become the biggest foreign investors in Macao. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Yimin Zhang said this at the 5th anniversary meeting of The Macao Chinese Enterprises Association.  The Inland Investment Enterprises in Macao grew from small to big, from weak to strong, and have now become one of the important strengths in Macao's economic area. </seg>
<seg id=5> These enterprises make an important contribution to Macao's prosperity and steadiness. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It is presented that these enterprises are widely involved in many Macao industries and their managements, such as business and trade, industry, finance, insurance, tourism, restaurants, transportation, construction, real estate, etc. </seg>
<seg id=7> Their holdings among these industries, finance and insurance accounts for 50%, tourism accounts for 50-70%, imports and exports account for 30%, real estate accounts for 70%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Yimin Zhang expressed that, Macao Chinese Enterprises will continue to follow Deng Xia Ping's "one country two systems" ideals, while following the governments specific policies regarding Hong Kong and Macao, continuing to follow the regulations of "what is allowable and what is not allowable".  Through working hard together with local people and industries, Macao Chinese Enterprises will make more contributions to strengthening Macao's economic support and developing Macao's society. </seg>
</p>
